text: Puskus Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Puskus is a name derived from the Choctaw language meaning "baby". Variant names are "Puscoos Creek", "Puscus Creek", "Puscuss Creek", and "Puss Cuss Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Lafayette County, Mississippi
title: Puskus Creek
